{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"c750eb0960e029df836e56dc77bb8c148fcf5723"},"timestamp":1271080749,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyODQ4NTE2","github-url":"https://github.com/parrot/parrot/issues/319","origin":"github"},"title":"[DEPRECATION] ManagedStruct automatic resize on shape change","message":"Changing the shape of a struct can occur for reasons other than the desire to reallocate, for example, when trying to view contents as different datatypes (emulating perl's pack/unpack).\n\nAlso reshapes can take several steps. Reallocating each step is suboptimal. In stead, an allocate/reallocate method should be called after the reshaping is complete to reallocate to the new desired shape.\n\nOriginally http://trac.parrot.org/parrot/ticket/1554","files":null}]}